# Component Patterns

## Directory Structure

```
src/components/
├── ui/              → shadcn/ui primitives (auto-generated, do not manually edit)
├── forms/           → Form components (login-form.tsx, signup-form.tsx)
├── layout/          → Layout components (sidebar.tsx, header.tsx, footer.tsx)
└── [feature]/       → Feature-specific composed components
```

## shadcn/ui — Always Use First

Each Next.js app (web, admin) has its own independent shadcn/ui installation.

**Before building any UI element, check if shadcn/ui has a component for it.** If a shadcn component exists (or a close equivalent), install and use it. Never hand-roll dropdowns, dialogs, popovers, tooltips, selects, tabs, accordions, or other standard UI patterns when shadcn provides them.

### Decision Flow

1. Need a UI pattern (dropdown, popover, dialog, sheet, etc.)?
2. Check the shadcn/ui registry: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components
3. If it exists → install with `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` from the app directory
4. Compose the shadcn primitive into your feature component
5. Only build custom UI when no shadcn equivalent exists

### Common Mappings

| UI Pattern | shadcn Component |
|---|---|
| Dropdown / context menu | `DropdownMenu` |
| Modal / confirmation | `Dialog` |
| Side panel / drawer | `Sheet` |
| Tooltip | `Tooltip` |
| Popover | `Popover` |
| Tabs | `Tabs` |
| Select / combobox | `Select` or `Command` |
| Accordion / collapsible | `Accordion` or `Collapsible` |
| Toast / notification | `Sonner` or `Toast` |
| Data table | `Table` + `DataTable` |
| Form inputs | `Input`, `Textarea`, `Checkbox`, `Switch`, `RadioGroup` |

### Adding Components

```bash
# From the app directory
cd apps/web
npx shadcn@latest add button card dialog dropdown-menu

cd apps/admin
npx shadcn@latest add button data-table
```

### Do NOT

- Manually edit files in `components/ui/` — they are managed by shadcn CLI
- Copy shadcn components between apps — install independently per app
- Import shadcn components from one app into another
- Hand-roll UI patterns that shadcn already provides (dropdowns, popovers, dialogs, etc.)
- Use raw Radix primitives directly — use the shadcn wrapper which applies consistent styling

## Component Conventions

- One component per file
- File naming: **kebab-case** (`user-profile-card.tsx`)
- Component naming: **PascalCase** (`UserProfileCard`)
- Colocate component-specific types in the same file
- Extract shared types to a `types.ts` file when used by 3+ components

## Composition

- Prefer composition over prop-drilling
- Use shadcn primitives as building blocks for feature components
- Feature components import from `@/components/ui/` and compose them

## Server vs Client Components

- **Default to Server Components** in Next.js
- Add `"use client"` only when the component needs:
  - Event handlers (`onClick`, `onChange`, etc.)
  - React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, etc.)
  - Browser APIs (`window`, `localStorage`, etc.)
- Keep client components as small and leaf-level as possible
